nodes.bodyText:
Hello @ijuma
I assume you are writing about security_config.py kafka_opts function:
Is it correct?
If yes, then it seems all options are supported in java since JDK7 or even earlier:
Can you, please, clarify, what specific jvm options should be fixed?
https://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/technotes/guides/security/jgss/tutorials/LoginConfigFile.html
    @property
    def kafka_opts(self, node):
        if self.has_sasl:
            if self.static_jaas_conf:
                return "\"-Djava.security.auth.login.config=%s -Djava.security.krb5.conf=%s\"" % (SecurityConfig.JAAS_CONF_PATH, SecurityConfig.KRB5CONF_PATH)
            else:
                return "\"-Djava.security.krb5.conf=%s\"" % SecurityConfig.KRB5CONF_PATH
        else:
            return ""

